
# Byte-identical canon — preserve exact bytes, no CRLF conversion. Updated 2026-06-20 (session 5)
# for the expanded Frontier Claude Code Kit: the glob covers every byte-identical canon file
# (the 7 kit docs + examples/) so a checkout never CRLF-mangles them. (Our own editable canon files
# — README.md, ULTRON_INSTANTIATION.md — are pinned too; harmless, just disables autocrlf there.)
docs/canon/** -text

# Enforcement hook scripts — force LF so node/git-bash run them correctly under core.autocrlf=true (BR-21.4).
.claude/hooks/*.mjs text eol=lf
.claude/hooks/*.sh text eol=lf
